# PR Message Convention

`language = "en"`

## Title

```
<Prefix>: <one-line summary>
```

- Same prefix list as commits (`commit-message-format.en.mdc`)
- ~50 characters max; avoid vague wording

## Body (required sections)

```markdown
## Summary
<!-- Why this PR is needed, 1–3 sentences -->

## Changes
<!-- Bullet list of meaningful changes -->

## Technical details
<!-- Design decisions; write "None" if N/A -->

## Test plan
<!-- What was verified; if not tested, state why -->

## Related issues
<!-- Closes #123 / Refs #456; or "None" -->
```

## Generation Rules

1. Use **diff** (`git diff [base]...HEAD`), **commit history**, and **related issues** as input
2. Do not duplicate Summary and Changes (Summary = Why, Changes = What)
3. If tests were not run, explain in Test plan

## Prohibited

- Unstructured wall-of-text titles or bodies
- Describing changes not present in the diff
- Emojis

## Example

**Title:** `feat: add Box/SharePoint data source selector UI`

**Body:**

```markdown
## Summary
Allow users to choose Box or SharePoint as the flow data source on the settings screen.

## Changes
- Add radio selector for data source type
- Conditionally show SharePoint fields when selected

## Technical details
None

## Test plan
- [x] Box selection shows folder input
- [x] SharePoint selection shows site URL input

## Related issues
Refs #12
```
